{
  "text": "In another study; Hwang D, Jeon K-H, et al. [CITATION_1] included more than 100 consecutive patients with LAD stenosis who underwent both PET scan and invasive physiological assessment then optimal cut-off values of FFR, IFR, and resting Pd/Pa were assessed using PETderived coronary flow reserve (CFR) and relative flow reserve (RFR) as references. The overall diagnostic accuracy of FFR, IFR, and resting Pd/Pa was not different for CFR < 2.0 (nearly FFR 70%, iFR 74%, and resting Pd/Pa 70%) and RFR < 0.75 (nearly FFR 74%, IFR 71%, and resting Pd/Pa 75%). Also, this concordance continued in large patient outcome trials conducted on both tests especially DEFINE-FLAIR [CITATION_2] and IFR SWEDE-HEART [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
